      "section_path": [
        "1. CyberSafeKids Report: A Life Behind The Screens"
      ],
      "ordinal": 3,
      "text": "This highlights the popularity of certain free to use (and in some cases paid) apps and games with minors, which must be considered under the Digital Fairness Act. Examples of the most popular of these are WhatsApp, Snapchat, TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, Roblox, Fortnite, Minecraft and EA FC. All of these currently contain exploitative practices and dark patterns, which minors must be protected from. In the section From Pray to Prey: Invisible Forces Manipulating Children concerns relating to game mechanics, recommender algorithms in VSPs and the lack of safeguards in AI chatbots are highlighted.",
